views.text: Welcome to the Tavern, a public, all-ages chatroom! Here you can chat about productivity and ask questions. Have fun!
Welcome to the Inn! Pull up a chair to chat, or take a break from your tasks.

Need a break? Check into Daniel’s Inn to pause some of Habitica’s more difficult game mechanics:

 • Missed Dailies won’t damage you
 • Tasks won’t lose streaks or decay in color
 • Bosses won’t do damage for your missed Dailies
 • Your boss damage or collection quest items will stay pending until check-out
Habitica tries to create a welcoming environment for users of all ages and backgrounds, especially in public spaces like the Tavern. If you have any questions, please consult our guidelines.
The colored usernames you see in chat represent a person’s contributor tier. The higher the tier, the more the person has contributed to habitica through art, code, the community, or more!

I've tried rewards this month but I have to say I didn't really use it. I tend to take breaks from work, and go for a walk without requiring rewards.

I prefer not to buy to skip or mark a daily as it's against my objective with habitica.

@jsandovalc I can really relate to that. I actually changed one of reward to (Key to library Amaza) which costs me 9000 coins. I plan to reward myself a book from amazon if I can stay productive all month long without missing any dailies except for Sundays

@Pandawalker yep, anyone can submit ideas for quests on the Trello board. Habitica admins select one of the submissions, so it can be fairly slow since there's at most one new quest per month. It took me about a year for my first one to be accepted, and another year for the second one, and that's been it.
